{% comment %}
  snippets/icon-plus.liquid
  ------------------------------------------------------------------
  "+" popup-trigger icon for sections/product-grid.liquid's grid tile
  marker. Rendered via {% render 'icon-plus' %}, same pattern as
  icon-hamburger/icon-close in banner.liquid.

  Kept as an inline-SVG snippet (not an <img src="asset_url">) for the
  same reason noted in product-grid.liquid: a theme-wide button/pseudo
  -element reset can silently strip generated content, but can't strip
  markup that's actually in the DOM. `stroke="currentColor"` (instead
  of a hardcoded "black") so the icon's color can still be themed via
  CSS `color` on the trigger button if that's ever needed.

  Source: plus.svg (10x10, two crossed strokes, stroke-width 1.5).
{% endcomment %}
<svg class="icon-plus" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
  <path d="M4.98047 0.75V9.21154" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
  <path d="M0.75 4.98071H9.21154" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
